LTI Systems
===========
x(t)-->System-->y(t)

Properties of Linear Systems
----------------------------
1. Scaling
	x(t) -> y(t)
2. Superposition
	x(t)=x1(t)+x2(t) -> y(t)=y1(t)+y2(t)

Properties of Time Invariant Systems
------------------------------------
x(t)->y(t)
x(t-T)->y(t-T)

Examples
--------
Moving Average Filter
y(n)=(1/3)(x(n-1)+x(n)+x(n+1))
Low Pass filter--removes noise

Median Filter
y(n)=med(x[n-1],x[n],x[n+1])
Advantage over moving average--cancels huge noise
Time Invariant but not Linear (no superposition)
